07: | Phase 4 | `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestConstants -v` |\n308: | Phase 5 | `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py sdk-python/tests/test_data_plane.py sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py -v` |\n309: | Phase 6 | `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py -v` |\n310: | Phase 7 | `python -c \"from agentcube.utils import DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, SESSION_HEADER, make_timeout_tuple; print('OK')\"` |\n311: | All Tests | `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py -v --cov=agentcube.utils.http` |\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ## Acceptance Criteria\n316: \n317: - [ ] `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120` constant defined\n318: - [ ] `DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0` constant defined\n319: - [ ] `DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS = 10` constant defined\n320: - [ ] `DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE = 10` constant defined\n321: - [ ] `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` constant defined\n322: - [ ] `CONTENT_TYPE_JSON = \"application/json\"` constant defined\n323: - [ ] `AUTH_HEADER = \"Authorization\"` constant defined\n324: - [ ] `create_session` accepts `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `headers`, `retry_config` kwargs\n325: - [ ] `RetryConfig` dataclass with `max_retries`, `backoff_factor`, `retry_on` fields\n326: - [ ] `DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG` with `max_retries=3`, `backoff_factor=0.5`\n327: - [ ] `RetryHTTPAdapter` retries on 5xx status codes (500, 502, 503, 504)\n328: - [ ] `RetryHTTPAdapter` retries on `ConnectionError`, `Timeout` exceptions\n329: - [ ] `RetryHTTPAdapter` implements exponential backoff\n330: - [ ] `make_timeout_tuple(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` returns `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n331: - [ ] `make_timeout_tuple` uses defaults when arguments are `None`\n332: - [ ] `is_retryable_error(exception)` returns `True` for retryable exceptions\n333: - [ ] `is_retryable_status(status_code)` returns `True` for 5xx codes\n334: - [ ] All clients (`ControlPlaneClient`, data plane clients) use imported constants\n335: - [ ] All 20 unit tests pass\n336: - [ ] `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` exports new constants and functions\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## File Changes Summary\n341: \n342: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n343: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n344: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py` | Modify | +120 | Add constants, RetryConfig, RetryHTTPAdapter, helper functions |\n345: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Modify | +10 | Export new constants and functions |\n346: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Modify | -8 | Use imported constants instead of local |\n347: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Modify | -8 | Use imported constants instead of local |\n348: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Modify | -8 | Use imported constants instead of local |\n349: | `sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py` | Create | ~180 | HTTP utilities unit tests |\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Implementation Notes\n354: \n355: ### Constants Pattern\n356: \n357: All HTTP-related constants should be defined in `agentcube/utils/http.py`:\n358: \n359: ```python\n360: DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n361: DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0\n362: DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS = 10\n363: DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE = 10\n364: SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n365: CONTENT_TYPE_JSON = \"application/json\"\n366: AUTH_HEADER = \"Authorization\"\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ### RetryConfig Dataclass\n370: \n371: ```python\n372: from dataclasses import dataclass\n373: from typing import Set, Tuple\n374: \n375: @dataclass\n376: class RetryConfig:\n377:     max_retries: int = 3\n378:     backoff_factor: float = 0.5\n379:     retry_on_status: Tuple[int, ...] = (500, 502, 503, 504)\n380:     retry_on_errors: Tuple[type, ...] = (ConnectionError, requests.Timeout)\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ### RetryHTTPAdapter\n384: \n385: ```python\n386: class RetryHTTPAdapter(HTTPAdapter):\n387:     def __init__(self, retry_config: RetryConfig = DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG, **kwargs):\n388:         super().__init__(**kwargs)\n389:         self.retry_config = retry_config\n390:     \n391:     def send(self, request, **kwargs):\n392:         for attempt in range(self.retry_config.max_retries + 1):\n393:             try:\n394:                 response = super().send(request, **kwargs)\n395:                 if response.status_code not in self.retry_config.retry_on_status:\n396:                     return response\n397:                 if attempt < self.retry_config.max_retries:\n398:                     time.sleep(self.retry_config.backoff_factor * (2 ** attempt))\n399:                     continue\n400:                 return response\n401:             except self.retry_config.retry_on_errors:\n402:                 if attempt < self.retry_config.max_retries:\n403:                     time.sleep(self.retry_config.backoff_factor * (2 ** attempt))\n404:                     continue\n405:                 raise\n406: ```\n407: \n408: ### Helper Functions\n409: \n410: ```python\n411: def make_timeout_tuple(\n412:     connect_timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n413:     read_timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n414: ) -> Tuple[float, float]:\n415:     return (\n416:         connect_timeout if connect_timeout is not None else DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT,\n417:         read_timeout if read_timeout is not None else DEFAULT_TIMEOUT,\n418:     )\n419: \n420: def is_retryable_error(exc: Exception) -> bool:\n421:     return isinstance(exc, (ConnectionError, requests.Timeout))\n422: \n423: def is_retryable_status(status_code: int) -> bool:\n424:     return status_code >= 500 and status_code < 600\n425: ```\n426: \n427: ### Client Constants Migration\n428: \n429: Replace local constants with imported ones:\n430: \n431: ```python\n432: # Before (in each client):\n433: DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n434: DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0\n435: \n436: # After:\n437: from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT, SESSION_HEADER\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## Implementation Timeline\n443: \n444: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n445: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n446: | Phase 1: Constants | T1.1-T1.7 | Pending | 0% |\n447: | Phase 2: Retry Handler | T2.1-T2.6 | Pending | 0% |\n448: | Phase 3: Helper Functions | T3.1-T3.4 | Pending | 0% |\n449: | Phase 4: Session Headers | T4.1-T4.3 | Pending | 0% |\n450: | Phase 5: Client Updates | T5.1-T5.3 | Pending | 0% |\n451: | Phase 6: Unit Tests | T6.1-T6.20 | Pending | 0% |\n452: | Phase 7: Export Update | T7.1 | Pending | 0% |\n453: \n454: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/47 tasks)**\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## References\n459: \n460: - Design: `changes/AR-029/design.md`\n461: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md`\n462: - Proposal: `changes/AR-029/proposal.md`\n463: - Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n464: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n465: - Related AR: `changes/AR-028/tasks.md` (AgentRuntimeClient)\n\n(End of file - total 465 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 ŌĆö SDK HTTP Õ║ĢÕ▒éÕ«óµłĘń½» Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-029 ŌĆö SDK HTTP Õ║ĢÕ▒éÕ«óµłĘń½» |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: HTTP Session Configuration (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120` constant in `http.py`\n  - Purpose: Define default read timeout constant","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775883352222,"end":1775883352257}}}}
